Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (180 degrees C). Grease a 9 inch square pan. Mix 1 cup flour, white sugar and butter by hand. Pat into pan. Bake for 8 - 10 minutes. With a whisk, beat 2 eggs. Whisk in brown sugar, then add 1/4 cup flour and baking powder. Stir in nuts and cherries. Pour over baked crust. Bake for 20 - 25 minutes more.